[[File:שמעון אליטוב.JPG|thumb|Rabbi Shimon Elituv]]
'''Shimon Gad Elituv''' ({{lang-he-n|'''שמעון גד אליטוב'''}}; born 24 February 1937) is an [[Israel]]i [[rabbi]] and member of the [[Mateh Binyamin Regional Council]], the Chief Rabbinate Council, rabbi of Mevasseret Zion, chairman of the Committee of Rabbis and communities in the Diaspora and Jerusalem rabbis of [[Chabad-Lubavitch]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://shturem.org/index.php?section=news&id=30996 |author=shturem.org |title=Rabbi Shimon Elituv Inaugurated to Council |accessdate=3 August 2016}}</ref>

He served for ten years as rabbi of the Halabi Community "sukkah of David" in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]].<ref>[http://www.shturem.org/index.php?section=news&id=31260]</ref>

